CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in New Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, September 9, 1972, pg. 1 reads: "Join Our Struggle - Demonstrators who assembled outside Western Penitentiary in support of the Sept. 5th work stoppage are asking those who wish to "quietly" support the strike, do so by calling, writing, or sending a telegram to their state legislators-making it known that the public backs the strike. (Harris Photo)
TitMainTitle: Demonstrators protesting prison conditions, including sign reading "Stop the usage of dungeon," standing on train tracks along Ohio River near Western Penitentiary
